PHP Transaction Client v1.6.1 API Specification
SUMMARY:  INNER | FIELD | CONSTR | METHOD DETAIL:  FIELD | CONSTR | METHOD

Class TransactionRequest

The TransactionRequest object is used for all transactions.

To properly understand the role of class TransactionRequest, please read the Overview document.

public TransactionRequest()
Method Detail

clearError

clearError()
Clears the current error text. This method should not be used directly by the merchant. It is used internally after a setter succeeds.
Returns:
 void

 

doTransaction

doTransaction()
Attempts to perform a credit card transaction. Call this method after calling all the setters for a credit card transaction. This will return false if there was a communication error while attempting the transaction.
Returns:
 TransactionResponse

 

doBatchTransaction

doBatchTransaction()
Attempts to perform a batch action. Call this method after calling all the setters for a batch action. This will return false if there was a communication error while attempting the transaction.
Returns:
TransactionResponse

 

executeTransaction

executeTransaction()
This method should not be called directly. It is used internally by doTransaction() and doBatchTransaction() to communicate with the transaction server.
Returns:
 TransactionResponse

setChargeTotal

setChargeTotal(Double $argChargeTotal)
Sets the total charge amount for the credit card transaction. This should be in the form of a decimal number with at most two decimal places. The following are valid:
$ccRequest->setChargeTotal(1.99); // $1.99
$ccRequest->setChargeTotal("1.99"); // $1.99
$ccRequest->setChargeTotal("1"); // $1.00
$ccRequest->setChargeTotal("1.1"); // $1.10
$ccRequest->setChargeTotal(0.10); // $0.10

Parameters:
Double $argChargeTotal
Returns:
 Boolean

 

setChargeType

setChargeType(String $argChargeType)
Sets the charge type. Charge Type applies to credit card transactions only. It must be one of (case sensitive):
  • AUTH
  • CAPTURE
  • SALE
  • VOID
  • CREDIT
  • VOID_AUTH
  • VOID_CAPTURE
  • VOID_CREDIT
  • CREATE_ORDER
  • CANCEL_ORDER
  • CLOSE_ORDER

Parameters:
String $argChargeType - The type of credit card transaction to perform.
Returns:
 Boolean

setExpireMonth

setExpireMonth(Integer $argExpireMonth)
Sets the credit card expiry month. This must be a one or two digit number either in string or integer form between 1-12.
$ccRequest->setExpireMonth(1); // January
$ccRequest->setExpireMonth("1"); // January
$ccRequest->setExpireMonth("12"); // December

Parameters:
Integer $argExpireMonth
Returns:
 Boolean

 

setExpireYear

setExpireYear(Integer $argExpireYear)
Sets the credit card expiry year. Must be a four digit number in string or integer form.
$ccRequest->setExpireYear(2005); // Valid
$ccRequest->setExpireYear("2005"); // Valid
$ccRequest->setExpireYear("05"); // Invalid!

Parameters:
Integer $argExpireYear - Description
Returns:
 Boolean

setOrderID

setOrderID(String $argOrderID)
Sets the order ID (this must be unique). The constraints on this field depend on the account type you have on the Paygateway Payment Service. If you do not provide an order ID, one will be generated for you and returned in the TransactionResponse object.

Parameters:
String $argOrderID - A unique ID to identify this order.
Returns:
 Boolean

setReferenceID

Parameters:
String $argReferenceID - Reference ID as returned in the TransactionResponse object.

 Boolean

setVersionID

setVersionID(String $argVersionID)
Sets the version ID of the plug sending the transaction. This method should not be called directly. The PHP plug uses it internally. You may use the corresponding getter to retrieve the current version of the PHP Transaction Client.

Parameters:
String $argVersionID
Returns:
 Boolean

 

setTransactionType

setTransactionType(String $argTransactionType)
Sets the transaction type. This method should not be called directly by the merchant. It is used by the PHP Transaction Client to differentiate between batch and credit card transactions. Valid transaction types are (case sensitive):
  • CREDIT_CARD
  • BATCH

Parameters:
String $argTransactionType
Returns:
 Boolean
